I am boy living in NEO hostel. Why is there no hot water in my hostel?
Last year seniors got good hostel and it was 500usd only and this year you gave us the worst hostel and still 600usd, I don't understand this logic.. in this small room that looks like nest, we 8 people are living but last year I heard in this room just there were 6 people. But we can adjust.
Now the point is, for past 1 month we managed without hot water. It was so difficult, I got fever and cold.

But now it started to snow.. how do you think we will manage in cold water when it's freezing cold outside? Will you live in this kind of condition?

Hot water comes after 12 am
At night when all students are supposed to sleep. But I used to be awake just to bath between 12-1, then I sleep at 2 only.
Then morning I can't wake up and go to class, and having bad cold because of bathing that late night. My sleep and studies is getting interrupted.
This is how difficult it is... Do You understand right now?

Dear student

I hope this message finds you well. I want to sincerely thank you for bringing to our attention the difficulties you and your fellow residents are facing at thehostel. Your wellbeing is of utmost importance to us.

I am pleased to inform you that we are taking immediate action to address these concerns. We have initiated the installation of new boilers to ensure a consistent supply of hot water. Additionally, to provide further comfort during the cold weather, heaters are being installed in all rooms.

Please be assured that we are working diligently to ensure these installations are completed as swiftly as possible. Your patience and understanding during this period are greatly appreciated.

We understand the inconvenience and discomfort caused by the current conditions, and we are committed to ensuring that you and your peers have a comfortable and safe living environment. Should you have any further concerns or if there’s anything else we can assist you with, please do not hesitate to contact us.

Thank you for your patience and cooperation.

Best regards,
